commit.message:
Merge pull request #5 from frerich/build_with_hp_2014.2.0.0

Fix building with current Haskell Platform (2014.2.0.0)

Fix building with current Haskell Platform (2014.2.0.0)

According to https://www.haskell.org/platform/changelog.html the latest
Haskell Platform (2014.2.0.0) ships with newer versions of a few
packages we need. Let's bump our upper bounds accordingly. In
particular, we need to bump the upper bounds of base, array and
template-haskell.

No actual code changes seem to be required.
Display a colored king icon in the title of the client based on whose turn it is. Resolves issue #4.
Fix instructions in README.txt (previous ones worked inadvertently on my machine due to the dependencies already being installed).
Added cabal file, and added build directions to README.txt
Slightly tersify part of ChessBackend.
Added message to standard out indicating the port when the server is started.
Implemented castling.
Added onFailDo, intended to be used with castling logic.
Remove some spurious blue highlightings.
Changed the highlighting color of the destination squares to green, and added blue highlighting for the source square.

Fixed bugs involving moves being buffered/piece selection persisting across turns. Fixed bug involving DisplayPlayerID after stalemate/checkmate. Re-enabled client-side logging (invisible by default, can be displayed by devtools, with all messages retroactively visible).
Added support for moving pieces by clicking and dragging (in addition to clicking the source, then the destination).
Added server-side display of moves made. Fixed a bug where moves were working in Firefox but not in Chrome/IE.
Added screenshot demonstrating 4 instances of the client running (with 2 seperate games of chess), demonstrating the tilesize feature.
Added tilesize initialization based on the URL.
Added screenshot of two instances of the client running.
Change web-page title, removed testing string.
Added checkmate & stalemate detection.
Added mechanism for determining when someone is in check (and prevent moving into check / remaining in check).
Added pawn promotion (currently automatically to queen).
Added a keepalive thread to avoid silent disconnections (which seemed to be occurring after a minute, and seem to be fixed with this change).
Added message to be displayed when there is a disconnect.
Added "Heads up display" of who each person is playing as, and whose turn it currently is.
Fixed desynchronization issues for multiplayer chess. (It's currently possible to inadvertantly enqueue (at least) one action, but that's a comparatively minor bug).
Added 2-player mode. Currently Black (the second player to join) has a smooth connection, and White is a few frames off (which adds up).
Fixed pawn movement/capture. Commented out logging of received JSON.
Revised/simplified mechanism for submitting moves (significantly less finicky now).
Added mechanism for submitting moves (works, but is kind of finicky).
Fix logic bugs with knight/{rook,bishop,queen} movements. Introduce board storage in the form of IORefs.
